
### **4\. Deploy the 8896-MTU Patched Workload Manifest**

\[\!NOTE\] Workload Pods using the DRA API bypass the GKE multi-network controller's MTU injection phase. To successfully unblock the 8896 MTU Jumbo Frame ceiling, applications must inject the **`NET_ADMIN`** capability and tune their internal Linux link MTUs in their container entrypoint.

```
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: iperf-dranet-v10
  labels:
    app: iperf-dranet-v10
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: iperf-dranet-v10
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: iperf-dranet-v10
    spec:
      tolerations:
      - key: "nvidia.com/gpu"
        operator: "Exists"
        effect: "NoSchedule"
      affinity:
        nodeAffinity:
          requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
            nodeSelectorTerms:
            - matchExpressions:
              - key: cloud.google.com/gke-nodepool
                operator: In
                values:
                - chavoshi-v10-pool
        podAntiAffinity:
          requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
          - labelSelector:
              matchExpressions:
              - key: app
                operator: In
                values:
                - iperf-dranet-v10
            topologyKey: "kubernetes.io/hostname"
      containers:
      - name: net-tester
        image: ubuntu:latest
        securityContext:
          capabilities:
            add: ["NET_ADMIN"]
        command: ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
        args:
        - |
          apt update && apt install -y iperf3 iproute2 net-tools iputils-ping
          ip link set eth1 mtu 8896
          ip link set eth2 mtu 8896
          iperf3 -s -D
          sleep 3600
        resources:
          claims:
          - name: netdev-claim
      resourceClaims:
      - name: netdev-claim
        resourceClaimTemplateName: netdev-claim-template
```

